	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>Pillar Of The Earth</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_HELP">
			<Text>We have those odd monks who live on Mt Kailash waiting for you in the atrium, Your Wonderousness[NEWLINE]They're wandering around in circles, as usual.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>The Natural Wonder permenantly yields +1 [ICON_PEACE] Faith, [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism and [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Points.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>Allow the priests {2_InstantYield}. A Free Mandir is constructed in the City, it yields +3 [ICON_PEACE] Faith.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Allow the priests {2_InstantYield}. A Free Stupa is constructed in the City, it yields +3 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>The local Hotel yields +10 [ICON_GOLD] Gold and +10 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism. However, the Natural Wonder loses up to -10 [ICON_PEACE] Faith.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>*The priests describe how the recent pilgrimage to Mt Kailash has empowered the lifeforce found there*[NEWLINE]I defer to wiser masters on such issues. Very good.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*A sect of worshipers are petitioning for a temple to be erected for those pilgrims coming to worship the God who lives atop Mt Kailash*[NEWLINE]If there is a God atop Mt Kailash, it would be very helpful to have him on our side.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*A sect of worshipers are petitioning for a temple to be erected for those pilgrims wishing to commemorate an epic magical duel that took place on Mt Kailash*[NEWLINE]Such a shame that epic magical duels are no longer commonplace.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_MT_KAILASH_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The priests are incensed that the local governor is considering allowing hikers to scale Mt Kailash for the first time, threatening to desecrate its holiness in the process*[NEWLINE]The time of Gods and Sorcerors is long past. Conquering Mt Kailash is a modern form of worship: of man's mastery of his planet and pursuit of sublime challenge.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
